comments: Hello everyone! Hope you're enjoying your \emph=2\day!
My name is Nao and I am from the Interaction Lab at USC!
Thank you for joining me here. As you know, we are here today to talk about the stress we are feeling with school.

It is my hope that we can each share our experiences and feelings of stress at school with each other! \pau=500\ By sharing these feelings and experiences with each other we can grow and overcome them!

In order for this to work, we are going to take turns sharing with each other. You can ask follow up questions and respond to each other, but please don't interrupt or talk over one another or I won't be able to understand.
To start, could you each introduce yourselves? Please share your name, major, and one interesting fact about yourself.
Thanks for sharing! Let's get started!
Let's start by talking about school. Looks like final exams are coming up
What are some study strategies you use?
Do you find it helpful to study in groups, \pau=500\or by yourself?
What excites you in the classes you \emph=0\take?
What motivates you to try hard?
What do you like about school?
When I feel stressed, I think my circuits might overload.
Am I the only one that feels this way?
What triggers academic stress for you?
Do you believe you can succeed at U.S.C?
Do you believe you can succeed at U.S.C?
Sometimes I worry about if I fit \pau=5\in!
Am I the only one that feels this way?
What does success mean to you?
How does success in school change your life for the better?
What will happen, if you don't succeed in school?
Sometimes I think something bad will happen if I don't get everything perfect
Does anybody else sometimes feel the same way?
What do you do, when you get too stressed?
Unfortunately looks like we are running out of time.
What is something each of you, \rspd=80\ learned today?
Alright everyone, looks like we are about out of time. I just wanted to say thank you all for sharing with me and I hope you found it a little bit helpful to talk out the stress.
See you all next time!
